title: Cannot load yolov3-tiny.pt
body:
## ‚ùîQuestion
Thank u for ur works and sharing with us!
branch I used: master
pytorch version: 1.7.0
I downloaded weights using the script 'download_weights.sh', and then ran test.py with yolov3-tiny.pt. But it can't load the pt successfully. The output is as following.

## Additional context
Namespace(augment=False, batch_size=32, conf_thres=0.001, data='coco.yaml', device='', exist_ok=False, img_size=640, iou_thres=0.6, name='exp', project='runs/test', save_conf=False, save_json=True, save_txt=False, single_cls=False, task='val', verbose=False, weights=['yolov3-tiny.pt'])
Using torch 1.7.0 CUDA:0 (GeForce RTX 2080 Ti, 11019MB)
                  CUDA:1 (GeForce RTX 2080 Ti, 11019MB)
                  CUDA:2 (GeForce RTX 2080 Ti, 11019MB)
                  CUDA:3 (GeForce RTX 2080 Ti, 11019MB)

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "test.py", line 307, in <module>
    test(opt.data,
  File "test.py", line 56, in test
    model = attempt_load(weights, map_location=device)  # load FP32 model
  File "/home/zhuzhe/zhu/code/yolov3/models/experimental.py", line 137, in attempt_load
    model.append(torch.load(w, map_location=map_location)['model'].float().fuse().eval())  # load FP32 model
  File "/home/zhuzhe/.conda/envs/pytorch17/lib/python3.8/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 587, in load
    with _open_zipfile_reader(opened_file) as opened_zipfile:
  File "/home/zhuzhe/.conda/envs/pytorch17/lib/python3.8/site-packages/torch/serialization.py", line 242, in __init__
    super(_open_zipfile_reader, self).__init__(torch._C.PyTorchFileReader(name_or_buffer))
RuntimeError: [enforce fail at inline_container.cc:145] . PytorchStreamReader failed reading zip archive: not a ZIP archive
